Definition: an open recess in a wall at the base of a chimney where a fire can be built
Example: the fireplace was so large you could walk inside it; he laid a fire in the hearth and lit it; the hearth was black with the charcoal of many fires
Synonyms: hearth, open_fireplace, recess, chimney, p, an, open, in, a, wall, at, the, base, of, where, fire, can, be, built, was, so, large, you, could, walk, inside, it, he, laid, and, lit, black, with, charcoal, many, fires
Category: noun.artifact
